Chullpa Marka - - This is the spine-like ridge south of junction of the Río Aguilani and Río Miguillas where we first discovered the ruins of Choquecamiri. Collections made by Virgilio Kuno in the ruins area. 19 km N. of Choquetanga. The area is covered with shrubs and small trees and burned grasslands. Acacia is dominant. At my request the local campesinos have stopped burning this as of 1988, and the area is returning to forest rapidly.
